design:
In nvim/.config/nvim/lua/kickstart/plugins/sidekick.lua, add a tool cmd override in setup:
  cli = { tools = { claude = { cmd = { 'claude', '<flags>' } } } }
The existing toggle_tool('claude') already calls cli.toggle({ name='claude', focus=true }), so it will pick up the configured cmd. IMPORTANT: cli.toggle does NOT accept an inline cmd/args -- custom args MUST be defined as the named tool's cmd in setup(). The tool spec 'cmd' field is an array of command + args strings (e.g. { 'claude', '--model', 'opus' }).
